description: A woman is treated by paramedics after collapsing following a fire in the kitchen of her Renfrewshire home.
title: Woman collapses after kitchen fire in Kilbarchan
title_page: Woman collapses after kitchen fire in Kilbarchan - BBC News
maintext:
A woman has been treated by paramedics after collapsing following a fire in the kitchen of her Renfrewshire home.
Fire crews were called to the flat in Wheatlands Drive, Kilbarchan, at about 20:15 on Monday.
They extinguished the blaze and provided treatment to the woman while awaiting paramedics. She did not need to go to hospital.
The fire service said an early 999 call meant crews were able to prevent the blaze from spreading to other rooms.
